# Zero-Based Documentation Numbering

When writing or editing project documentation, use zero-based numbering for numbered lists and numbered headings.

Preferred format:

```text
0) First item
1) Second item
2) Third item
```

Use the same convention for numbered headings in docs:

```text
0) Overview
1) Setup
2) Troubleshooting
```

Avoid one-based numbering such as `1)`, `2)`, `3)` when starting a new sequence in documentation.
